Phase 2: Requirement Analysis Phase
Functional Requirements:

The system must accept image uploads (JPG, PNG).

The AI must identify the Brand, Model, and Year range.

Technical output must include displacement, cooling type, and fuel system.

Non-Functional Requirements:

Reliability: Use exponential backoff to handle API rate limits.

User Interface: Must be responsive and accessible via mobile/web.

Security: API keys must be isolated via environment variables.

Software Requirements: Python 3.9, Streamlit 1.25+, Google-GenerativeAI SDK, Pillow.
